Section E -- IDE and Editor Plugin Exception

Notwithstanding the commercial use restrictions set forth in this License,
the Licensor hereby grants a limited, non-exclusive, royalty-free exception
to the commercial use prohibition solely under the following conditions:

E.1 Scope of Exception.

This exception applies exclusively to IDE extensions and editor plugins
(collectively, "Covered Extensions") that meet all of the following
criteria:

  (a) The Covered Extension is created, developed, owned, or officially
      published by Peko UI Technologies LLC; and

  (b) The Covered Extension's primary purpose is to provide editor or IDE
      integration for the PekoScript language, including but not limited
      to syntax highlighting, code completion, language server protocol
      (LSP) support, debugging integration, formatting, or linting within
      a text editor or integrated development environment; and

  (c) The Covered Extension is distributed through an official editor or
      IDE marketplace or extension registry (such as the Visual Studio
      Code Marketplace, JetBrains Marketplace, or equivalent).

E.2 Explicit Exclusions.

This exception does not apply to, and the commercial use restrictions of
this License remain in full force with respect to:

  (a) Command-line interface tools, terminal utilities, or shell
      integrations of any kind, including but not limited to the Peko
      CLI, build tools, package managers, compilers, or any tool invoked
      outside of an editor or IDE environment;

  (b) Software development kits (SDKs), libraries, frameworks, language
      bindings, or API wrappers intended for use by third-party developers
      in their own software;

  (c) Any extension, plugin, or tool created, owned, or published by a
      third party that is not Peko UI Technologies LLC;

  (d) Any product or service that incorporates the Licensed Work as part
      of a commercial offering, subscription service, or revenue-generating
      product, even if such product includes editor or IDE functionality;

  (e) Any extension or plugin that competes directly with the Licensed Work
      or any Peko product or service.

E.3 Conditions of Exception.

Covered Extensions qualifying under Section E.1 must:

  (a) Include a notice in their documentation or marketplace listing
      stating that the extension utilizes software licensed under the
      Peko Source Available License 1.0; and

  (b) Not remove or obscure any copyright, trademark, or proprietary
      notices contained in the Licensed Work.

E.4 Revocation.

The Licensor reserves the right to revoke this exception at any time by
publishing an updated version of this License. Revocation shall not apply
retroactively to Covered Extensions already distributed prior to the
revocation date.

E.5 No Sublicensing.

This exception does not grant the right to sublicense the Licensed Work or
this exception to any third party.

